snippet.textDisplay:
Hey Casey. Can't deny it leaves a heavy heart after watching this, it got me thinking... I am coming 26 years old this May, indeed it is true that the year passes faster as each year goes by and how scary it seems, I never thought I would be as old as 25 back then (but hey look, I'm almost 26). Thank you Casey for reminding us - regardless of our age, we have to slow down to a stop and look around us, appreciate the things we are granted with TODAY, NOW.


I spent the last day of 2019 waking up in the hospital because of something that I thought would never ever (at least not so soon) happen to me, a heart attack. I was so scared when I woke up in one of the hospital bed, I felt weak, lost and scared because I couldn't recall what exactly had happened to me then and I was all alone... I hope no one else would ever have to go through whatever I had went through and that we will learn to appreciate life more each day.


Happy new year folks!
